{
    "modName": "Worn Legendary Items",
    "displayName": "Worn Legendary Items",
    "minMcmVersion": 2,
    "content": [
        {
            "text": "Chance of the enemy's weapon being made legendary",
            "type": "slider",
            "help": "The percent chance that the enemy's weapon is chosen as the legendary item instead of a piece of their armor",
            "valueOptions": {
                "min": 0,
                "max": 100,
                "step": 1,
                "sourceType": "GlobalValue",
                "sourceForm": "Worn Legendary Items.esp|005"
            }
        },
        {
            "text": "Chance of adding a new legendary weapon",
            "type": "slider",
            "help": "The percent chance that if the enemy's weapon is going to be made legendary, it will be a new weapon from the legendary leveled lists",
            "valueOptions": {
                "min": 0,
                "max": 100,
                "step": 1,
                "sourceType": "GlobalValue",
                "sourceForm": "Worn Legendary Items.esp|006"
            }
        },
        {
            "text": "Chance of adding a new legendary armor piece",
            "type": "slider",
            "help": "The percent chance that if the enemy's armor is going to be made legendary, it will be new armor from the legendary leveled lists",
            "valueOptions": {
                "min": 0,
                "max": 100,
                "step": 1,
                "sourceType": "GlobalValue",
                "sourceForm": "Worn Legendary Items.esp|007"
            }
        },
        {
            "text": "Add a new legendary item if no equipment can be made legendary",
            "type": "switcher",
            "help": "Necessary to continue adding legendary items for legendary creatures and robots",
            "valueOptions": {
                "sourceType": "GlobalValue",
                "sourceForm": "Worn Legendary Items.esp|001"
            },
            "groupControl": 1
        },
        {
            "type": "spacer",
            "numLines": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "Advanced Options",
            "type": "section"
        },
        {
            "text": "Strictly enforce legendary weapon chance for NPCs",
            "type": "switcher",
            "help": "If an equipped weapon should be made legendary but none are eligible, generate a new one instead of making legendary armor",
            "valueOptions": {
                "sourceType": "GlobalValue",
                "sourceForm": "Worn Legendary Items.esp|009"
            }
        },
        {
            "text": "Strictly enforce legendary weapon chance for creatures/robots",
            "type": "switcher",
            "help": "Use the configured weapon chance for generated legendaries instead of the base game's chances",
            "valueOptions": {
                "sourceType": "GlobalValue",
                "sourceForm": "Worn Legendary Items.esp|00D"
            },
            "groupCondition": 1
        },
        {
            "type": "spacer",
            "numLines": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "Turning It Up to 11",
            "type": "section"
        },
        {
            "text": "These settings may drastically alter the game's balance or could result in enemies visually unequipping and equipping their armor shortly after you see them. They can be fun, but use at your own discretion.",
            "type": "text"
        },
        {
            "text": "Maximum number of legendary items per legendary enemy",
            "type": "slider",
            "help": "A random number of legendaries between 1 and this value will be added to each legendary enemy",
            "valueOptions": {
                "min": 1,
                "max": 3,
                "step": 1,
                "sourceType": "GlobalValue",
                "sourceForm": "Worn Legendary Items.esp|00A"
            }
        },
        {
            "text": "Chance of normal enemies getting legendary items",
            "type": "slider",
            "help": "Useful if you are using mods that give normal and legendary enemies different equipment",
            "valueOptions": {
                "min": 0,
                "max": 10,
                "step": 1,
                "sourceType": "GlobalValue",
                "sourceForm": "Worn Legendary Items.esp|008"
            }
        }
    ],
    "pages": [
        {
            "pageDisplayName": "Eligible Equipment",
            "content": [
                {
                    "text": "Enemies are able to wear more types of equipment than can normally become legendary. By default, this equipment will never be made legendary, but these settings allow you to make them eligible. Note that many of these items likely do not have naming rules for legendary effects, so you will have to read their description to know what the effect does.",
                    "type": "text"
                },
                {
                    "text": "Clothing",
                    "type": "switcher",
                    "help": "Anything that can be upgraded with ballistic weave. May overlap with some of the other categories.",
                    "valueOptions": {
                        "sourceType": "PropertyValueBool",
                        "sourceForm": "Worn Legendary Items.esp|00C",
                        "propertyName": "ClothingEnabled"
                    },
                    "action": {
                        "type": "CallFunction",
                        "form": "Worn Legendary Items.esp|00C",
                        "function": "RefreshAllowedKeywords"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "text": "Headgear",
                    "type": "switcher",
                    "help": "Mostly helmets and gas masks, but includes a few hats and hoods (Keyword: ArmorBodyPartHead)",
                    "valueOptions": {
                        "sourceType": "PropertyValueBool",
                        "sourceForm": "Worn Legendary Items.esp|00C",
                        "propertyName": "HeadgearEnabled"
